Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cmput301f19t09.vibes.models.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MoodEvent

    public class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Represents an event in time. Models something that happened which has a date, time, and description. Implements serializable to be passable in intents.

        public Event(java.time.LocalDate date,
             java.time.LocalTime time,
             java.lang.String description)
        Creates a new Event object by accepting a date, time, and description.
        Parameters:
        date - Date of when the event occurred; should have the format ISO_LOCAL_DATE (yyyy-MM-dd).
        time - Time of when the event occurred; should have the format HH:mm.
        description - Describes the circumstances surrounding an event.

      • getEpochUTC

        public long getEpochUTC()
        Converts the combined date and time to its UTC epoch representation. An epoch is a an absolute time reference; the time since Midnight on the 1st of January 1970. Used for conversion into an acceptable format to store in firebase.
        Returns:
        Long UTC epoch representation of the combined date and time attribute.
